  "text": [
    "Hear me, O God!",
    "A broken heart",
    "Is my best part.",
    "Use still thy rod,",
    "That I may prove",
    "Therein thy Love.",
    "If thou hadst not",
    "Been stern to me,",
    "But left me free,",
    "I had forgot",
    "Myself and thee.",
    "For sin's so sweet,",
    "As minds ill-bent",
    "Rarely repent,",
    "Until they meet",
    "Their punishment.",
    "Who more can crave",
    "Than thou hast done?",
    "That gav'st a Son,",
    "To free a slave,",
    "First made of nought;",
    "With all since bought.",
    "Sin, Death, and Hell",
    "His glorious name",
    "Quite overcame,",
    "Yet I rebel",
    "And slight the same.",
    "But I'll come in",
    "Before my loss",
    "Me farther toss,",
    "As sure to win",
    "Under His cross."
  ],
  "title": "A Hymn to God the Father",
  "year": ""
